are detailed more in-depth (also see my <a href=\"https://github.com/guillaume-chevalier/SGNN-Self-Governing-Neural-Networks-Projection-Layer\">attempt to reproduce the paper in code</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/guillaume-chevalier/SGNN-Self-Governing-Neural-Networks-Projection-Layer\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">21</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":21,\"repo\":\"guillaume-chevalier/SGNN-Self-Governing-Neural-Networks-Projection-Layer\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> and watch <a href=\"https://vimeo.com/305197775\">the talks' recording</a>).</li>","updatedAt":"2018-12-31T22:59:57.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"guillaume-chevalier/Awesome-Deep-Learning-Resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Practical Resources</h2><h3>Some Datasets</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/1803.05449\">SentEval: An Evaluation Toolkit for Universal Sentence Representations</a> - A Python framework to benchmark your sentence representations on many datasets (NLP tasks).</li>","updatedAt":"2018-12-31T22:50:24.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"guillaume-chevalier/Awesome-Deep-Learning-Resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Practical Resources</h2><h3>Some Datasets</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/1705.06476\">ParlAI: A Dialog Research Software Platform</a> - Another Python framework to benchmark your sentence representations on many datasets (NLP tasks).</li>","updatedAt":"2018-12-31T22:50:24.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"guillaume-chevalier/Awesome-Deep-Learning-Resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Practical Resources</h2><h3>Librairies and Implementations</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/guillaume-chevalier/SGNN-Self-Governing-Neural-Networks-Projection-Layer\">Self Governing Neural Networks (SGNN): the Projection Layer</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/guillaume-chevalier/SGNN-Self-Governing-Neural-Networks-Projection-Layer\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">21</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":21,\"repo\":\"guillaume-chevalier/SGNN-Self-Governing-Neural-Networks-Projection-Layer\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - With this, you can use words in your deep learning models without training nor loading embeddings.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-12-31T22:46:28.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"guillaume-chevalier/Awesome-Deep-Learning-Resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Posts and Articles</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://nlp.seas.harvard.edu/2018/04/03/attention.html\">The Annotated Transformer</a> - Good for understanding the \"Attention Is All You Need\" (AIAYN) paper.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-12-31T22:41:52.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"guillaume-chevalier/Awesome-Deep-Learning-Resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Papers</h2><h3>Other</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/1606.04080\">Matching Networks for One Shot Learning</a> - Classify a new example from a list of other examples (without definitive categories) and with low-data per classification task, but lots of data for lots of similar classification tasks - it seems better than siamese networks. To sum up: with Matching Networks, you can optimize directly for a cosine similarity between examples (like a self-attention product would match) which is passed to the softmax directly. I guess that Matching Networks could probably be used as with negative-sampling softmax training in word2vec's CBOW or Skip-gram without having to do any context embedding lookups.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-12-31T22:34:09.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"guillaume-chevalier/Awesome-Deep-Learning-Resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Papers</h2><h3>Other</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/1708.00630\">ProjectionNet: Learning Efficient On-Device Deep Networks Using Neural Projections</a> - Replace word embeddings by word projections in your deep neural networks, which doesn't require a pre-extracted dictionnary nor storing embedding matrices.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-12-31T22:28:26.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"DopplerHQ/awesome-interview-questions","categoryHTML":"<h2>Blockchain</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.edureka.co/blog/interview-questions/blockchain-interview-questions/\">Top 55 Blockchain Interview Questions You Must Prepare In 2018</a></li>","updatedAt":"2018-12-31T13:51:50.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"DopplerHQ/awesome-interview-questions","categoryHTML":"<h2>Blockchain</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://mindmajix.com/blockchain-interview-questions\">Blockchain Interview Questions</a></li>","updatedAt":"2018-12-31T13:51:50.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"DopplerHQ/awesome-interview-questions","categoryHTML":"<h2>Blockchain</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://intellipaat.com/interview-question/blockchain-interview-questions/\">Top Blockchain Interview Questions</a></li>","updatedAt":"2018-12-31T13:51:50.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"DopplerHQ/awesome-interview-questions","categoryHTML":"<h2>Blockchain</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://applicature.com/blog/blockchain-interview-questions\">Blockchain Develo